packed.translate: упакованный, фасованный, уплотненный, переполненный, слежавшийся, скученный
examples: Fans packed the stadium.
Are all your things packed?
The island was packed with tourists.
She packed her lunch in a paper bag.
Oranges are packed full of vitamin C.
The nurse packed gauze in the wound.
Thousands of people packed into the mosque.
A great many people packed into the church.
She packed her things and left.
The crowd packed the auditorium.
The crowd packed the auditorium.
After one year, I packed in university.
The book is packed with useful information.
The show has been playing to packed houses since it opened.
50,000 fans packed into the stadium.
I packed a bag and organized some food.
The murder trial packed the court house.
Kelly packed her things before breakfast.
The bar was packed to the gills on Monday.
The car was packed and we were ready to roll.
Breakable articles should be packed carefully.
Everything's packed, and we're ready to leave.
We were packed as tight as sardines on the bus.
Glass must be packed in several layers of paper.
Most of the holidaymakers had packed up and gone.
I packed my remaining possessions into the trunk.
She packed her suitcases the night before she left.
There were 20 people packed inside of her dorm room.
Her bag was light, packed with only the bare essentials.

В этой книге полным-полно полезных сведений.
